#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""
codex.py

Run from inside a git repo, even if this script lives outside it:

    sudo cp vybe /usr/bin/vybe && sudo chmod +x /usr/bin/vybe
    (^ install)
    cd my-repo
    python3 ../codex.py

Features:
- Long-running prompt loop
- Multiline Codex task input
- Submit multiline task input with 4 blank lines in a row
- Runs `codex exec` in a temp snapshot of the repo
- Shows summary + changed files
- apply / reject / inspect flow
- Per-file or single commit mode
- Pushes to remote after apply
- Repo root resolved from CURRENT WORKING DIRECTORY
- Filters ignored/generated files from change detection
- Big low-flicker radar/matrix animation while Codex runs
- Static matrix-style panel before input, without breaking typing

Notes:
- Use an HTTPS token/PAT, not a password.
- Do not commit this script with real secrets inside it.
"""

